advantage. You should remember that White must try to return the pawn under
the most favourable circumstances and that's what 0.01% of players, including
GM J. Polgar, would do here.} 16. Bc7 $1 {First this move!. Because Judit
evaluated that the exchange 18.Bxb6 is going to be in her favour.} Rd7 17. d6
$1 exd6 18. Bxb6 $1 {Very accurate play by Judit.} Qxb6 19. Nd5 Qa7 20. Nec3 {
Attacking the g4 knight and preparing the transfer of the knight to the b5
square.} Qxd4 21. h3 {After this move Judit wins the exchange.} Nh6 22. Qxd4
